AUTHORS OF THE LATIN' HYMNS

AMBROSE, ST. (340-397), Bishop of Milan, is justly styled “the Father of Church-song in the West.'' He be- came, like St. Hilary, a great champion of orthodoxy against the Arians in the West. And it was while he and his faithful flock were besieged in his Cathedral by the im- perial troops that, as St. Augustine tells us, he first com-- posed hymns for them to sing “lest they faint through fatigue of sorro .’' The simple, austere hymns of St. Mffiays been considered the ideal in Church- song.
